        public ImprovementCollaborator(java.lang.String id,
                               java.lang.String fullName,
                               java.lang.String email,
                               java.lang.String extension)

        ImprovementCollaborator

        Description: Constructs a new ImprovementCollaborator object with the provided information. This constructor initializes the ImprovementCollaborator object with the provided ID, full name, email, and extension. Additionally, it initializes the ArrayList of led projects.

        Preconditions:

        • The id, fullName, email, and extension parameters must be of type String.

        Postconditions:

        • A new ImprovementCollaborator object is created with the provided ID, full name, email, and extension.
        • An ArrayList of led projects is initialized.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the collaborator.
        fullName - The full name of the collaborator.
        email - The email address of the collaborator.
        extension - The extension number of the collaborator (optional).

    • Method Detail

      • createProject

        public java.lang.String createProject(java.lang.String name,
                                      int intPriority,
                                      Request acceptedRequest,
                                      int intImpactedCommunity,
                                      int intKnowledgeType)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new knowledge management project based on the provided details. This method generates a unique ID for the project using generateRandomUniqueCode(). It then creates a new knowledge management project with the given name, priority, collaborator as leader, accepted request, impacted community, and knowledge type. The project is added to the list of led projects (ledProjects).

        Preconditions:

        • The ledProjects list must be initialized.
        • acceptedRequest must not be null.
        • name must be a String.
        • intPriority, intImpactedCommunity, and intKnowledgeType must be valid integers form the displayed values.

        Postconditions:

        • A new knowledge management project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a unique ID, name, priority, leader, accepted request, impacted community, and knowledge type.
        • The project is added to the list of led projects.
        • A message indicating the successful registration of the project is returned.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the project.
        intPriority - The priority level of the project.
        acceptedRequest - The accepted request for the project.
        intImpactedCommunity - The index representing the impacted community for the project.
        intKnowledgeType - The index representing the type of knowledge project.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the successful registration of the knowledge management project.

      • createProject

        public java.lang.String createProject(java.lang.String name,
                                      int intPriority,
                                      Request acceptedRequest,
                                      java.lang.String processCode)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new transformation and improvement project based on the provided details. This method generates a unique ID for the project using generateRandomUniqueCode(). It then creates a new improvement project with the given name, priority, collaborator as leader, accepted request, and process code. The project is added to the list of led projects (ledProjects).

        Preconditions:

        • The ledProjects list must be initialized.
        • acceptedRequest must not be null.
        • name and processCode must be a String.
        • intPriority must be a valid integer.

        Postconditions:

        • A new transformation and improvement project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a unique ID, name, priority, leader, accepted request, and process code.
        • The project is added to the list of led projects.
        • A message indicating the successful registration of the project is returned.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the project.
        intPriority - The priority level of the project.
        acceptedRequest - The accepted request for the project.
        processCode - The process code for the improvement project.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the successful registration of the transformation and improvement project.

      • searchProject

        public Project searchProject(java.lang.String id)

        searchProject

        Description: Searches for a project in the list of led projects based on the provided ID. This method iterates through the list of led projects (ledProjects) to find the project with the specified ID.

        Preconditions:

        • The ledProjects list must be initialized.
        • id must not be null.

        Postconditions:

        • If a project with the specified ID is found in the list of led projects, it is returned.
        • If no project with the specified ID is found, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the project to search for.
        Returns:
        The project with the specified ID if found, otherwise null.

      • generateRandomUniqueCode

        public java.lang.String generateRandomUniqueCode()

        generateRandomUniqueCode

        Description: Generates a random unique code for identifying projects. This method generates a random code consisting of four alphanumeric characters from the set of allowed characters. It ensures that the generated code is unique by checking if a project with the same code already exists using searchProject(String).

        Preconditions:

        • The ledProjects list must be initialized.
        • The searchProject method must be implemented to search for projects by code.

        Postconditions:

        • A random unique code is generated and returned.
        Returns:
        A random unique code for identifying projects.
